I"à]<h1 id="latex-and-sublime-text">LaTeX and Sublime Text</h1>

<p>This tutorial explains how to use $\LaTeX$ in the text editor <a href="https://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text</a> and how to set up code snippets to write faster. For a general introduction to $\LaTeX$, see e.g. <a href="https://www.overleaf.com/learn/latex/Learn_LaTeX_in_30_minutes">this tutorial by Overleaf</a>. This setup is inspired by <a href="https://castel.dev/post/lecture-notes-1/">this article by Gilles Castel</a>, where a similar setup for Linux is described (using Vim as a text editor). On Windows, however, it is easier to set everything up in Sublime Text.</p>

<center><img src="/img/2021-07-17-latex-and-sublime-text/LaTeX_Sublime_Text.png" width="100%" /></center>

<p><strong>Contents:</strong></p>

